OL,4,Cpoverty in the area
OL,6,F"Income in the family may go down
OL,7,Fbecause you have to entertain them and
OL,8,Ffeed them. So we work with our local
OL,9,Fschools. This week we have supplied 32
OL,10,Fbags to our local schools."
OL,12,FWith the town only having one main
OL,13,Fsupermarket, Pat Boyd says
OL,14,Ftransporting food can be a challenge.
OL,15,FShe said: "The towns, they have more
OL,16,Fchoice of shops and things, whereas
OL,17,Fwe've got to pay top price. The price
OL,18,Fhas gone up, and you have to think
OL,19,Ftwice about some things."
